How does the do...while statement differ from the while statement?
The do...while statement guarantees that the code within the curly braces will execute at least once, whereas the while statement does not.
The while statement executes a block of code until a condition is true, whereas the do...while statement executes a block of code while (for as long as) a condition is true.
The while statement executes a block of code until a condition is true, whereas the do...while statement executes a block of code while (for as long as) a condition is true.
The while statement guarantees that the code within the curly braces will execute at least once, whereas the do...while statement does not.
